SPATE: Developing Security Architecture for these pillars

  - Services

  - People (Skills)

  - Activities (processes)

  - Technology

  - Environment 


Enterprise Governance Vs. Information Security Governance

  - Excersize of responsibilities and practices to: (Entrprise Governance)
    - Provide strategic direction
    - Ensure objectives area achieved
    - Determine appropriate risk management
    - Verify responsible use of resources 

- Subset of enterprise governance that: (Information Security Governance)
    - Provides strategic direction for security objectives
    - Ensures that objectives are achieved
    - Ensures that information security risk is appropriately managed
    - Effectively and efficient use of enterprise information resources.
